      "type": "Annotation",
      "body": [
        {
          "type": "TextualBody",
          "purpose": "transcribing",
          "value": "DAYS PASS and the years vanish, and we walk sightless among miracles.\nGod, fill our eyes with seeing and our minds with knowing;\nlet there be moments when Your Presence, like lightning,\nillumines the darkness in which we walk.\nHelp us to see, wherever we gaze, that the bush burns unconsumed.\nAnd we, clay touched by God, will reach out for holiness, and exclaim in wonder:\nHow filled with awe is this place, and we did not know it!\nBlessed is the Eternal One, the Holy God!\nבָּרוּךְ אַתָּה, יְיָ, הָאֵל הַקָּדוֹשׁ.\nBaruch atah, Adonai, Ha-El hakadosh.",
          "language": "en"
        }
      ],
      "created": "2026-07-15T15:00:48.226Z",
      "creator": {
        "isGuest": true,
        "id": "chigpSIK8rYaUli95Qqx"
